Rating: 4
You really can't go wrong with this recipe. I make it for every Christmas and then again for Valentine's Day for presents. I suggest you make it exactly how the recipe says; then try your own variations. For example, I like using matzo crackers the best (I buy them right after each Passover and stock up). I also buy candy bars (heath, today it wa butterfinger crisps) and crush them up and use them instead of walnuts. I always make two batches, one has to have shredded coconut. Another tip: since I know I am going to make these each Christmas, I stock up on Halloween candy (after halloween, to stock my supply for Christmas holidays.) Lastly, I too have had success using only 1 stick of butter.

