Rating: 0
I've made a recipe similar to this for Passover, using matzo boards instead of graham crackers. As I recall, my recipe uses an equal amount of butter and brown sugar (3/4 cup of each, I believe). The original recipe called for a little less of both, but it's best if you have a lot of the toffee coating the crackers. That way the toffee saturates the crackers and you won't taste any dry or gritty taste. Very good and easy!

